4. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://quest5.net/wiki/Verbtemplate_element">http://quest5.net/wiki/Verbtemplate_element</a><!-- m -->

maybe you can figure out yourself how to do both functionalities, without having to create~add~write~code in both a Command and a Verb.[/quote:2q7h7ec9]

I have tried this and my problems are almost completely solved when using both command and a verb. It feels much more natural, so thanks for explaining this in so much detail <!-- s:) --><img src="{SMILIES_PATH}/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><!-- s:) --> I really dont mind extra work as long as it works. The only annoyance I still have left is the &quot;Error running script&#058; No verb response defined&quot; message which I want to change to: &quot;I dont understand your command. Try rephrasing.&quot; I have checked the whole filtered library list 3 times and I can't find this line anywhere. Any ideas where to look? I do not think the player would like errors popping out in their games, so I find &quot;I dont understand your command. Try rephrasing.&quot; much better explanation.

The line pops out when I use incomplete commands, such as: &quot;hide under the&quot;
It also pops out when i try something like: &quot;hit hallway table&quot;
&quot;Error running script&#058; No verb response defined&quot;

PS. I think there might be something messed up with my code due to all the changes I made. Can you perhaps take a look at it? Here is the code and just in case I also attached the game file:

